comments: As Walker (BOS) is retreating, Butler (MIA) releases from the contact during his drive on the perimeter.
Butler (MIA) slides his arm across Tatum's (BOS) body as marginal contact occurs during his drive.
Butler (MIA) jumps toward Tatum (BOS) to contest the jump shot attempt and would land in front of him. Tatum extends his leg into Butler.
Adebayo (MIA) makes clean contact to the ball as he defend Brown's (BOS) pass attempt.
Crowder (MIA) moves alongside Walker's (BOS) path as marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Herro (MIA) brushes Walker's (BOS) arm, causing marginal contact to occur at the end of his drive and does not affect his SQBR.
Crowder (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position and cleanly blocks Walker's (BOS) shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Adebayo (MIA) receives the pass and maintains his pivot foot.
Walker (BOS) places and removes his resting hand from Butler's (MIA) arm prior to his upward shooting motion.

While Jones Jr. (MIA) is already driving toward Smart (BOS), who is in a legal guarding position in his path before the contact, Walker (BOS) veers into Jones Jr., increasing his momentum and driving him through Smart's space.
Tatum (BOS) briefly engages and separates from Jones Jr. (MIA) after the pick.
Jones Jr. (MIA) retracts his resting hand from Tatum (BOS) as Tatum releases toward the pass.
Tatum (BOS) gathers the ball on his right foot while progressing and hops on the same foot, and then lifts his pivot foot before releasing his dribble.
Williams (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Herro's (MIA) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Adebayo (MIA) brushes Brown's (BOS) arm after he has released his tip shot near the rim, and the contact is marginal.
Crowder (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (BOS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.

Replay review of the foul called on Walker (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Walker (BOS) does not maintain a legal guarding position and moves laterally into Butler's (MIA) path.
During the inbound, Williams (BOS) and Adebayo (MIA) briefly engage and separate.
Williams (BOS) brushes the ball and Adebayo's (MIA) hand simultaneously after the catch.
Dragic (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Smart's (BOS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Walker (BOS) places a resting hand on Herro's (MIA) hip and the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) and Adebayo (MIA) engage and separate during the rebound.
Adebayo (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Tatum (BOS) during his drive and fadeaway jump shot attempt.
During the rebound, Crowder (MIA) and Brown (BOS) mutually engage and separate.
During the defensive switch, marginal contact occurs as Smart (BOS) and Herro (MIA) briefly engage and separate.
Brown (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Butler (MIA).
Dragic (MIA) cleanly deflects the basketball, any additional foot-to-foot contact with Walker (BOS) is deemed to be incidental.
During the pick, Iguodala (MIA) briefly engages and separates from Brown (BOS).
During the pass, Crowder (MIA) extends his foot out to make contact with the ball.
At the end of his drive, Walker (BOS) releases from the contact and does not extend his arm or deliver contact to Herro (MIA).
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Tatum's (BOS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Tatum (BOS) makes contact to Butler's (MIA) arm during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
After the screen, Williams (BOS) and Iguodala (MIA) briefly engage and separate.
Adebayo (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Tatum (BOS) and cleanly blocks the shot.
Williams (BOS) commits a take foul on Adebayo (MIA).
Tatum (BOS) goes to the floor under his own power and legally stands up while in possession of the ball.
Butler (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position while defending Tatum (BOS) through the pass and catch.
Butler (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Tatum (BOS).
